1
00:00:06,080 --> 00:00:07,372
Administer adrenaline.

2
00:00:07,372 --> 00:00:08,575
Got it!

3
00:00:15,482 --> 00:00:17,088
Checking the waveform.

4
00:00:17,088 --> 00:00:18,349
Kid, prep the DC.

5
00:00:18,349 --> 00:00:19,550
Right!

6
00:00:23,695 --> 00:00:24,902
Shocking now.

7
00:00:24,994 --> 00:00:26,200
Clear!

8
00:00:41,106 --> 00:00:42,317
Heartbeat restored.

9
00:00:42,526 --> 00:00:43,912
Blood pressure dropping.

10
00:00:43,912 --> 00:00:46,970
- Transfusion and noradrenaline bolus, now.
- Yes, Doctor.

11
00:00:50,611 --> 00:00:52,657
You've improved, Dr. Yakushiji.

12
00:00:58,167 --> 00:01:00,233
I've finally graduated from Kid.

13
00:01:01,713 --> 00:01:03,171
Preparing for intubation.

14
00:01:04,366 --> 00:01:05,566
Ow!

15
00:01:11,060 --> 00:01:12,265
Come on...

16
00:01:14,292 --> 00:01:15,505
But still...

17
00:01:17,809 --> 00:01:20,455
That was a nice dream.

18
00:01:21,393 --> 00:01:22,593
It's like a dream!

19
00:01:22,593 --> 00:01:25,419
You really mean I can be
Head of the Medical Department?!

20
00:01:25,419 --> 00:01:26,954
Could you handle it?

21
00:01:28,866 --> 00:01:29,979
Of course!

22
00:01:29,979 --> 00:01:32,227
Leave it all to me,
Kongo Matayoshi!

23
00:01:32,227 --> 00:01:33,599
Thank you.

24
00:01:34,100 --> 00:01:39,300
This way, we can promote cooperation
between Emergency and other departments.

25
00:01:39,432 --> 00:01:40,832
Wait a moment!

26
00:01:41,359 --> 00:01:45,521
Weren't we shutting down Emergency
to cut losses for the new hospital?

27
00:01:46,305 --> 00:01:49,745
We recently heard from Fink.

28
00:01:50,286 --> 00:01:55,139
They've agreed to support the new hospital
on the condition we keep Emergency open.

29
00:01:55,619 --> 00:01:57,535
Why the sudden change of heart?

30
00:01:57,680 --> 00:02:02,565
Dr. Bonten honestly revealed
that Anno saved Fink's life.

31
00:02:02,565 --> 00:02:07,595
Emergency's deficit is undeniable.
We should at least downsize it.

32
00:02:07,595 --> 00:02:10,092
No, quite the opposite.

33
00:02:10,092 --> 00:02:11,467
- The opposite?
- Yes.

34
00:02:11,467 --> 00:02:17,807
If Emergency accepts every patient
without refusal and saves them all,

35
00:02:17,834 --> 00:02:20,869
it will support the hospital's
overall profitability.

36
00:02:21,940 --> 00:02:23,413
What do you mean by that?

37
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:27,032
If Emergency accepts
and saves every patient,

38
00:02:27,032 --> 00:02:30,718
those patients can then receive
treatment from other departments.

39
00:02:30,799 --> 00:02:34,640
As a result, it boosts the hospital's
overall profitability.

40
00:02:34,640 --> 00:02:36,567
That's a great idea!

41
00:02:36,567 --> 00:02:37,892
No, wait, hold on!

42
00:02:38,119 --> 00:02:43,225
So we'd be taking on even more
patients from Emergency than before?

43
00:02:43,225 --> 00:02:45,065
- That's right.
- But that would...

44
00:02:45,065 --> 00:02:49,084
This is a job that only
you can do, Dr. Kongo.

45
00:02:50,546 --> 00:02:51,593
Huh?

46
00:02:51,593 --> 00:02:55,036
Please lend your expertise to Emergency.

47
00:03:00,859 --> 00:03:02,844
What? What are you planning?

48
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:08,108
At last, I'm a Head of Medicine!
Leave it all to me!

49
00:03:08,380 --> 00:03:09,996
I could become Taishaku's...

50
00:03:10,586 --> 00:03:15,114
No, even better! I could become
director of the new hospital!

51
00:03:15,206 --> 00:03:19,132
I must live up to
Director Tamon's expectations!

52
00:03:19,132 --> 00:03:21,292
Tamon! Come on!

53
00:03:24,086 --> 00:03:26,386
Another tough night shift, huh?

54
00:03:26,710 --> 00:03:30,276
I'm getting used to the pace,
but it's still exhausting.

55
00:03:30,440 --> 00:03:31,887
- Good work today.
- You too.

56
00:03:31,887 --> 00:03:33,441
Good work, everyone.

57
00:03:33,441 --> 00:03:34,821
Morning, everyone!

58
00:03:35,315 --> 00:03:36,602
Hey, listen up.

59
00:03:36,803 --> 00:03:39,602
The director just issued an order,

60
00:03:40,129 --> 00:03:44,660
and I'm back as Chief
of Emergency Medicine starting today!

61
00:03:44,660 --> 00:03:46,396
Really?

62
00:03:46,396 --> 00:03:49,371
No one but Dr. Daikoku should be
running Emergency Medicine.

63
00:03:49,371 --> 00:03:51,246
- Absolutely.
- Congratulations.

64
00:03:51,246 --> 00:03:54,766
Thanks. I'm counting on you too, Yakushiji.

65
00:03:55,436 --> 00:03:56,636
Me?

66
00:03:56,989 --> 00:03:58,526
Yes, sir! I'll do my best!

67
00:03:59,419 --> 00:04:02,449
Well then, new Chief,
we'll be on our way.

68
00:04:02,674 --> 00:04:04,933
- Good work.
- Good work today.

69
00:04:05,141 --> 00:04:07,713
Chief, we're heading to the ICU.

70
00:04:07,713 --> 00:04:09,013
Off you go!

71
00:04:10,940 --> 00:04:13,178
Oh! Anno, morning!

72
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:16,740
Dr. Anno, Dr. Daikoku's been appointed Chief.

73
00:04:16,740 --> 00:04:17,940
Huh.

74
00:04:25,346 --> 00:04:26,546
Incoming.

75
00:04:28,032 --> 00:04:29,066
Yes.

76
00:04:29,066 --> 00:04:32,857
Construction site collapse with injuries.
One adult. Requesting intake.

77
00:04:32,857 --> 00:04:34,183
Transport immediately.

78
00:04:34,649 --> 00:04:36,068
- Ten minutes.
- Got it!

79
00:04:37,430 --> 00:04:40,863
I did it in my dream.
I can do this!

80
00:04:41,526 --> 00:04:43,850
Can you tell me your name?
Excuse my touch.

81
00:04:46,843 --> 00:04:48,569
O2 sat at 85.

82
00:04:51,368 --> 00:04:52,574
Intubating.

83
00:04:52,941 --> 00:04:55,701
Wait, Kid.
Did you check for pneumothorax?

84
00:04:56,316 --> 00:04:58,844
I told you if the patient has
a tension pneumothorax,

85
00:04:58,844 --> 00:05:02,017
intubation with positive pressure
will cause cardiac arrest.

86
00:05:02,970 --> 00:05:06,078
Sorry, I forgot.
I'll auscultate right away.

87
00:05:10,356 --> 00:05:12,764
No pneumothorax. Intubating.

88
00:05:13,016 --> 00:05:14,221
Yes!

89
00:05:15,636 --> 00:05:16,785
Cardiac arrest!

90
00:05:16,785 --> 00:05:18,290
DC, now! Prep adrenaline!

91
00:05:18,290 --> 00:05:19,507
Yes!

92
00:05:27,133 --> 00:05:28,170
Hurry!

93
00:05:28,170 --> 00:05:29,373
Okay!

94
00:05:31,187 --> 00:05:32,236
Clear!

95
00:05:32,236 --> 00:05:33,474
Yes!

96
00:05:38,463 --> 00:05:39,563
Adrenaline, now!

97
00:05:39,563 --> 00:05:40,778
Got it!

98
00:05:41,623 --> 00:05:42,823
Adrenaline...

99
00:05:44,379 --> 00:05:45,779
Adrenaline!

100
00:05:48,989 --> 00:05:50,609
Administering adrenaline.

101
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:09,275
Heartbeat restored! BP's low!
Start transfusion and noradrenaline!

102
00:06:09,393 --> 00:06:10,610
Understood!

103
00:06:17,080 --> 00:06:21,022
I'm sorry, I'll fix this right away.

104
00:06:24,516 --> 00:06:25,881
I'm sorry.

105
00:06:35,799 --> 00:06:39,345
Dr. Ashura

106
00:06:41,810 --> 00:06:44,090
Good thing Surgery responded so quickly.

107
00:06:44,090 --> 00:06:46,863
But they accepted unusually fast
today, didn't they?

108
00:06:46,863 --> 00:06:49,063
True... Maybe there's a catch.

109
00:06:49,063 --> 00:06:52,566
Maybe Dr. Kongo's going to hit us
with another snide remark.

110
00:06:53,918 --> 00:06:54,949
Hey.

111
00:06:54,949 --> 00:06:56,285
Dr. Kongo!

112
00:06:56,312 --> 00:06:58,402
Hello, everyone. How are things?

113
00:06:58,402 --> 00:07:00,243
- Speak of the devil.
- Right?

114
00:07:00,243 --> 00:07:02,063
I can hear you, you know.

115
00:07:02,829 --> 00:07:04,669
Why are you in the ER?

116
00:07:04,683 --> 00:07:08,222
Oh, I was just passing by
and thought I'd pop in.

117
00:07:08,517 --> 00:07:11,683
Should the Chief of Surgery
be loafing around here?

118
00:07:11,683 --> 00:07:14,857
Chief of Surgery... loafing around.

119
00:07:16,459 --> 00:07:19,466
Loafing... Loafing?

120
00:07:20,783 --> 00:07:23,108
Head of the Medical Dept.
Dr. Kongo Matayoshi

121
00:07:23,108 --> 00:07:24,755
Head of the Medical Department?!

122
00:07:24,755 --> 00:07:28,222
Yes, Director Tamon personally
asked me to take the position.

123
00:07:28,222 --> 00:07:30,348
Why Dr. Kongo?

124
00:07:30,348 --> 00:07:32,230
Aren't there better candidates?

125
00:07:32,230 --> 00:07:33,447
I can hear you.

126
00:07:33,574 --> 00:07:37,816
It simply shows how much trust
Director Tamon places in me.

127
00:07:37,816 --> 00:07:43,503
As Head of the Medical Department,
I will bridge Surgery and Emergency,

128
00:07:43,503 --> 00:07:45,930
And I will... Hey!

129
00:07:46,469 --> 00:07:49,261
I will fully support everyone in Emergency.

130
00:07:49,261 --> 00:07:51,717
- You believe that?
- He may be up to something.

131
00:07:51,717 --> 00:07:53,056
I said I can hear you!

132
00:07:53,636 --> 00:07:58,671
We're all colleagues at this hospital.
Come to me anytime you need help.

133
00:08:02,708 --> 00:08:04,258
I can hear you!

134
00:08:06,213 --> 00:08:07,725
We didn't say anything.

135
00:08:07,725 --> 00:08:08,941
Not a word.

136
00:08:18,003 --> 00:08:20,010
Hey there.

137
00:08:22,392 --> 00:08:24,465
Still feeling down?

138
00:08:24,925 --> 00:08:26,389
No.

139
00:08:27,413 --> 00:08:30,673
The patient pulled through.
That's what matters, right?

140
00:08:31,065 --> 00:08:34,592
Thanks to everyone else, not me.

141
00:08:38,539 --> 00:08:43,049
In the end, I'm still just a rookie
holding everyone back.

142
00:08:47,984 --> 00:08:51,755
Hey, didn't you say you had plans today?

143
00:08:52,273 --> 00:08:53,809
Oh, right!

144
00:08:54,189 --> 00:08:55,528
I'm late!

145
00:08:57,439 --> 00:08:59,537
Was Dr. Yakushiji really that down?

146
00:08:59,537 --> 00:09:02,418
Yeah. He said he was dragging everyone down.

147
00:09:02,599 --> 00:09:06,455
He's surrounded by amazing doctors.
That probably makes it worse.

148
00:09:06,939 --> 00:09:11,819
He's a resident. Of course he can't
do everything. Nobody expects perfection.

149
00:09:12,138 --> 00:09:15,637
Exactly. He overthinks things.

150
00:09:16,766 --> 00:09:20,702
Poor thing. Maybe I should go cheer him up.

151
00:09:20,726 --> 00:09:25,458
Oh, he just left.
He's meeting a childhood friend.

152
00:09:26,613 --> 00:09:28,553
Well, he sounds just fine.

153
00:09:29,560 --> 00:09:31,303
What a waste of worry.

154
00:09:50,972 --> 00:09:52,033
Hey, Keita!

155
00:09:52,033 --> 00:09:54,027
Tamotsu, long time no see!

156
00:09:54,079 --> 00:09:56,384
- Sorry I'm late.
- Our table's over there.

157
00:09:56,384 --> 00:09:57,584
Thanks.

158
00:09:58,105 --> 00:09:59,445
Akane, Tamotsu's here.

159
00:10:00,055 --> 00:10:01,106
Huh?

160
00:10:01,106 --> 00:10:02,376
Come, sit down.

161
00:10:03,286 --> 00:10:05,400
Hello. Nice to meet you.

162
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:07,468
Hi. Who's she?

163
00:10:08,023 --> 00:10:10,875
Keita, come on.
Introduce me properly.

164
00:10:10,875 --> 00:10:13,173
Sorry, sorry. Let me introduce you.

165
00:10:14,446 --> 00:10:17,818
This is Akane Sawamura.
My fiancée.

166
00:10:18,266 --> 00:10:19,478
Fiancée?

167
00:10:20,942 --> 00:10:22,358
You're getting married?!

168
00:10:22,386 --> 00:10:23,605
Yep.

169
00:10:24,826 --> 00:10:26,933
You could've told me first!

170
00:10:27,433 --> 00:10:29,521
I wanted it to be a surprise.

171
00:10:31,671 --> 00:10:34,020
Excuse me. Can we order, please?

172
00:10:34,020 --> 00:10:35,228
Yes, sir.

173
00:10:36,947 --> 00:10:41,192
I'm sorry. I told him
I wanted to meet you.

174
00:10:41,192 --> 00:10:42,397
Me?

175
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:46,126
Keita always said he was proud
to be your best friend.

176
00:10:46,230 --> 00:10:48,201
- Two of these, please.
- Yes, sir.

177
00:10:49,633 --> 00:10:50,922
Tamotsu, beer's fine?

178
00:10:51,721 --> 00:10:52,995
Yeah, thanks.

179
00:10:53,019 --> 00:10:54,120
One draft, then.

180
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:55,332
Right away.

181
00:10:58,465 --> 00:11:00,057
Tamotsu, remember Beehive Park?

182
00:11:00,057 --> 00:11:02,204
Wow, that takes me back.

183
00:11:02,204 --> 00:11:04,849
There was this park called
Beehive Park near us.

184
00:11:04,849 --> 00:11:06,500
Enough about me.

185
00:11:07,353 --> 00:11:08,680
Keita, how've you been?

186
00:11:08,680 --> 00:11:13,640
Well, I got put in charge of launching
an overseas branch. It's been crazy.

187
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:15,773
Just got back to Japan yesterday.

188
00:11:15,773 --> 00:11:16,800
An overseas branch?

189
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:20,392
Yeah. Our president is seriously the worst.

190
00:11:20,440 --> 00:11:23,893
They threw me out there alone
with zero preparation.

191
00:11:23,893 --> 00:11:27,282
He'd call me screaming,
"I can't do this anymore!"

192
00:11:29,310 --> 00:11:32,420
I barely spoke the language
and knew nothing about the area.

193
00:11:32,420 --> 00:11:37,479
When I tried cold-calling like we do
in Japan, security chased me around.

194
00:11:38,117 --> 00:11:40,062
It was a total disaster.

195
00:11:40,080 --> 00:11:44,762
But after six months of struggling,
things finally started taking shape.

196
00:11:45,504 --> 00:11:46,911
That's amazing.

197
00:11:47,451 --> 00:11:50,914
Meanwhile, I'm just a resident...

198
00:11:52,319 --> 00:11:55,006
Kid, prep a transfusion.
Kid, stop the bleeding!

199
00:11:55,006 --> 00:11:56,326
I can't do this!

200
00:11:56,373 --> 00:11:57,879
This is beyond you.

201
00:11:57,904 --> 00:12:02,012
A novice who can't even treat patients alone
has no business worrying about me!

202
00:12:05,390 --> 00:12:07,807
You can't compare a doctor
and a businessman.

203
00:12:11,363 --> 00:12:12,981
It's from the president.

204
00:12:22,349 --> 00:12:27,560
Hey, Tamotsu,
why did you become a doctor?

205
00:12:28,393 --> 00:12:29,420
Huh?

206
00:12:29,420 --> 00:12:33,480
I mean, it's such a demanding job
with people's lives in your hands.

207
00:12:34,218 --> 00:12:36,577
So what made you want to pursue it?

208
00:12:40,490 --> 00:12:42,490
No good reason, really.

209
00:12:43,835 --> 00:12:48,096
My parents are doctors,
so I just sort of fell into it.

210
00:12:51,192 --> 00:12:54,828
Even so, the fact that
you made it is impressive.

211
00:13:00,520 --> 00:13:05,389
Well, as a doctor,
I've got a long way to go though.

212
00:13:08,128 --> 00:13:09,868
Sorry, sorry!

213
00:13:11,083 --> 00:13:13,067
So what were you talking about?

214
00:13:13,630 --> 00:13:14,844
Nothing.

215
00:13:14,903 --> 00:13:16,457
Huh? What's that about?

216
00:13:16,663 --> 00:13:17,870
It's a secret.

217
00:13:18,255 --> 00:13:19,856
What? Tell me!

218
00:13:20,022 --> 00:13:21,410
It was nothing important.

219
00:13:21,410 --> 00:13:22,629
Huh?

220
00:13:23,734 --> 00:13:25,367
You're putting it there?

221
00:13:25,367 --> 00:13:27,640
Perfect.

222
00:13:28,283 --> 00:13:29,323
Can he do it?

223
00:13:29,323 --> 00:13:30,843
Hey, looking pretty good!

224
00:13:31,403 --> 00:13:32,623
Looking good!

225
00:13:33,202 --> 00:13:34,230
I'm going all out.

226
00:13:34,230 --> 00:13:35,775
Wait, you're going all out?

227
00:13:35,775 --> 00:13:37,182
Here it comes!

228
00:13:37,188 --> 00:13:40,481
- Can you make it?
- Please, please, please!

229
00:13:41,303 --> 00:13:42,507
Ha!

230
00:13:43,116 --> 00:13:45,057
You did it!

231
00:13:46,736 --> 00:13:48,430
- Did it go in?
- It's in!

232
00:13:48,430 --> 00:13:50,029
- This way?
- That way!

233
00:13:50,029 --> 00:13:52,108
- Can you reach it?
- Of course I can!

234
00:13:52,156 --> 00:13:54,688
Oh right, right. Like this...
Okay, okay!

235
00:13:56,720 --> 00:13:57,750
Whoa! Nice!

236
00:13:57,750 --> 00:13:58,806
Whoa! Amazing!

237
00:13:58,806 --> 00:14:00,526
- I'm getting better!
- Yeah.

238
00:14:00,526 --> 00:14:01,569
Here, my treat.

239
00:14:01,569 --> 00:14:02,780
Oh, thanks!

240
00:14:07,576 --> 00:14:08,788
What's wrong?

241
00:14:08,830 --> 00:14:13,220
The flight back was so cramped,
my legs almost seized up.

242
00:14:18,603 --> 00:14:22,167
Akane seems really nice.

243
00:14:25,540 --> 00:14:27,360
I gotta step it up too.

244
00:14:29,899 --> 00:14:31,104
I'm rooting for you.

245
00:14:32,446 --> 00:14:33,685
Thanks!

246
00:14:45,876 --> 00:14:47,127
Tamotsu.

247
00:14:50,521 --> 00:14:54,085
I know it's tough having people's lives
in your hands,

248
00:14:55,723 --> 00:14:57,306
but I'm rooting for you.

249
00:15:01,449 --> 00:15:02,741
Thanks.

250
00:15:04,182 --> 00:15:05,835
Wait, I just said to you.

251
00:15:05,835 --> 00:15:07,042
Oh, right.

252
00:15:08,770 --> 00:15:10,430
Hey, we're about to start.

253
00:15:10,769 --> 00:15:12,892
Oh, let's do this then!

254
00:15:13,983 --> 00:15:17,337
- You've gotten good.
- We've been throwing a ton, after all.

255
00:15:17,662 --> 00:15:19,888
Taishaku General Hospital

256
00:15:22,150 --> 00:15:23,460
Good morning.

257
00:15:28,233 --> 00:15:29,495
Good morning.

258
00:15:29,960 --> 00:15:31,856
Good job working the night shift.

259
00:15:32,240 --> 00:15:33,868
Did you have fun yesterday?

260
00:15:34,100 --> 00:15:37,020
For the first time in a while,
I forgot about work.

261
00:15:37,020 --> 00:15:40,944
I think maybe I've been
overthinking everything.

262
00:15:41,065 --> 00:15:42,475
Really?

263
00:15:42,475 --> 00:15:46,042
Downtime is essential
for doing good work.

264
00:15:46,119 --> 00:15:49,465
Yes. I'll give it my all starting today.

265
00:15:49,853 --> 00:15:54,388
But you're just a resident,
so good enough is good enough.

266
00:15:54,519 --> 00:15:55,736
Huh?

267
00:15:55,979 --> 00:15:58,890
No point burning yourself out
and spinning your wheels.

268
00:16:00,365 --> 00:16:01,619
Right.

269
00:16:02,020 --> 00:16:04,940
Dr. Anno, the OR is prepped.
We're ready for you.

270
00:16:04,940 --> 00:16:06,302
Copy. On my way.

271
00:16:07,912 --> 00:16:10,126
I'm heading out too.
Hold down the fort.

272
00:16:10,126 --> 00:16:13,234
Sure. I'll go see the patients then.

273
00:16:13,807 --> 00:16:15,232
This'll be a bit cold.

274
00:16:16,074 --> 00:16:18,571
Ow ow ow ow!
It hurts!

275
00:16:19,188 --> 00:16:20,647
Intake form: Stomach pain

276
00:16:20,931 --> 00:16:23,301
Mr. Kobayashi, when did
the stomach pain start?

277
00:16:23,301 --> 00:16:25,600
Who cares? Just fix it!

278
00:16:25,600 --> 00:16:26,813
I'm sorry.

279
00:16:27,079 --> 00:16:28,328
It's gallstones.

280
00:16:28,328 --> 00:16:30,619
- G-Gallstones?
- We'll give you pain meds.

281
00:16:30,619 --> 00:16:31,842
Please do.

282
00:16:32,632 --> 00:16:33,848
Excuse me.

283
00:16:35,165 --> 00:16:36,199
Yes?

284
00:16:36,199 --> 00:16:38,154
Mr. Sakamoto's crashing in the ICU.

285
00:16:38,154 --> 00:16:40,174
- Crashing?
- Please come right away.

286
00:16:40,746 --> 00:16:44,125
Mr. Kobayashi,
could you wait just a bit longer?

287
00:16:45,047 --> 00:16:47,080
- Hurry up and do something!
- I'm sorry.

288
00:16:47,080 --> 00:16:50,052
I'll take over for you.

289
00:16:50,158 --> 00:16:52,620
No, I can't let you do this alone.

290
00:16:52,620 --> 00:16:55,953
I'll be fine.
Please let me handle it.

291
00:17:01,693 --> 00:17:04,389
Then call me immediately
if anything happens.

292
00:17:04,405 --> 00:17:05,612
Yes, sir.

293
00:17:08,183 --> 00:17:09,850
Do you have any allergies?

294
00:17:09,892 --> 00:17:12,386
Um, do you have any allergies or...

295
00:17:12,386 --> 00:17:14,800
I don't care, just hurry
and do something!

296
00:17:15,013 --> 00:17:16,227
I'm sorry.

297
00:17:17,875 --> 00:17:23,065
The pain looks pretty severe.
NSAIDs should do it.

298
00:17:30,906 --> 00:17:33,920
It'll kick in soon.
Just hold on a moment.

299
00:17:35,627 --> 00:17:36,905
Hey, Doc.

300
00:17:37,599 --> 00:17:38,851
Yes?

301
00:17:39,159 --> 00:17:40,385
Thanks.

302
00:17:44,684 --> 00:17:47,251
Doctor, there's a patient here
injured from a fall.

303
00:17:47,251 --> 00:17:48,485
I'll be right there.

304
00:17:48,516 --> 00:17:50,595
Mr. Kobayashi, please wait here.

305
00:18:00,169 --> 00:18:01,400
Done.

306
00:18:01,970 --> 00:18:03,340
That was intense.

307
00:18:03,900 --> 00:18:06,593
We got through it
thanks to you, Dr. Anno.

308
00:18:12,280 --> 00:18:13,506
Doctor?

309
00:18:15,917 --> 00:18:17,138
Incoming.

310
00:18:18,150 --> 00:18:19,309
Huh?

311
00:18:19,309 --> 00:18:20,517
Take care.

312
00:18:25,069 --> 00:18:27,073
Mr. Kobayashi, are you okay?

313
00:18:31,029 --> 00:18:32,253
Mr. Kobayashi?!

314
00:18:34,076 --> 00:18:36,395
Mr. Kobayashi, are you all right?

315
00:18:37,734 --> 00:18:39,020
Dr. Anno!

316
00:18:46,873 --> 00:18:49,994
Aspirin-induced asthma.
Hurry, or he'll stop breathing.

317
00:18:49,994 --> 00:18:52,368
Start oxygen. Prep the nebulizer.

318
00:18:52,564 --> 00:18:55,950
- Administering steroids. Prep adrenaline.
- Yes, Doctor.

319
00:19:29,697 --> 00:19:32,815
I tried to confirm his allergies properly.

320
00:19:33,839 --> 00:19:35,881
Mr. Kobayashi wouldn't tell me.

321
00:19:36,519 --> 00:19:39,750
If I'd known, I never
would've given him NSAIDs.

322
00:19:39,750 --> 00:19:41,328
It wasn't even in his chart.

323
00:19:41,328 --> 00:19:43,445
Excuses don't fly in life-or-death.

324
00:20:27,606 --> 00:20:32,692
Due to our error, we put Mr. Kobayashi
in a dangerous condition,

325
00:20:32,692 --> 00:20:35,542
and we are truly sorry.

326
00:20:38,474 --> 00:20:43,234
What is going on here?
My husband nearly died!

327
00:20:43,324 --> 00:20:46,055
We are truly sorry.

328
00:20:46,619 --> 00:20:51,089
You prioritized other patients
and left a resident in charge!

329
00:20:51,648 --> 00:20:54,534
How little do you value
my husband's life?

330
00:20:57,124 --> 00:21:02,444
I'm not asking for apologies.
I'm asking what you were thinking.

331
00:21:05,797 --> 00:21:10,410
Why won't you say anything?
Say something!

332
00:21:23,823 --> 00:21:25,360
Oh, good evening.

333
00:21:25,360 --> 00:21:26,616
Hello.

334
00:21:32,420 --> 00:21:35,440
How did it go with Mr. Kobayashi's family?

335
00:21:36,622 --> 00:21:40,408
Well, we managed
to settle things down somehow.

336
00:21:43,853 --> 00:21:45,673
And Dr. Yakushiji?

337
00:21:46,080 --> 00:21:48,197
I sent him home for today.

338
00:21:49,646 --> 00:21:51,065
Will he be okay?

339
00:21:53,307 --> 00:21:56,530
It was my fault
for leaving him alone.

340
00:21:57,659 --> 00:22:00,517
I feel terrible
for what I put Yakushiji through.

341
00:22:02,526 --> 00:22:06,015
Thanks to Dr. Anno, the patient's fine.

342
00:22:06,015 --> 00:22:09,205
I just hope he doesn't dwell on it too long.

343
00:22:09,926 --> 00:22:13,366
No, he'll be down for a while.

344
00:22:21,540 --> 00:22:25,344
Are you looking after
Dr. Yakushiji properly?

345
00:22:25,500 --> 00:22:26,717
Why should I?

346
00:22:27,778 --> 00:22:30,576
Supporting residents
is part of your job, isn't it?

347
00:22:31,278 --> 00:22:34,225
What if he quits because of this?

348
00:22:34,438 --> 00:22:36,800
Then he wasn't cut out
to be a doctor.

349
00:22:38,737 --> 00:22:40,457
That's colder than I expected.

350
00:22:40,484 --> 00:22:43,037
He'll decide on his own
whether to quit or stay.

351
00:22:43,893 --> 00:22:45,527
Maybe, but...

352
00:22:47,539 --> 00:22:52,639
Even you must have had someone
encourage you when you started out.

353
00:22:58,809 --> 00:23:01,791
Well, I think I'll go
grab some lunch too.

354
00:23:30,106 --> 00:23:34,084
The intubation tube may have shifted.
Doctor, please adjust it.

355
00:23:34,390 --> 00:23:35,614
Right.

356
00:23:36,769 --> 00:23:38,957
My husband almost died!

357
00:23:48,136 --> 00:23:49,360
Doctor.

358
00:23:59,220 --> 00:24:02,003
- What happened?
- The tube seems to have shifted.

359
00:24:02,003 --> 00:24:03,583
Got it. I'll adjust it.

360
00:24:06,276 --> 00:24:07,486
Move.

361
00:24:12,699 --> 00:24:13,914
Hold this.

362
00:24:39,939 --> 00:24:41,168
Resident.

363
00:24:43,168 --> 00:24:45,482
Oh, Director.

364
00:24:45,906 --> 00:24:46,941
Slacking off?

365
00:24:46,941 --> 00:24:48,392
No, I'm not slacking off.

366
00:24:48,823 --> 00:24:51,718
Well, maybe I am.

367
00:24:52,474 --> 00:24:53,514
Um...

368
00:24:53,514 --> 00:24:56,821
What is it? Did Anno chew you out again?

369
00:25:07,566 --> 00:25:12,946
I have no right to be
in Emergency Medicine anymore.

370
00:25:16,706 --> 00:25:18,165
I almost let...

371
00:25:20,418 --> 00:25:22,740
a patient die.

372
00:25:27,204 --> 00:25:29,603
I'm not even going into emergency medicine,

373
00:25:29,737 --> 00:25:34,824
so why do I have to go through
all this just for training?

374
00:25:38,612 --> 00:25:41,330
I'm just not cut out
for emergency medicine.

375
00:25:42,316 --> 00:25:43,529
I'm clumsy.

376
00:25:44,897 --> 00:25:45,931
I'm slow.

377
00:25:45,931 --> 00:25:48,770
Do you actually want to be
an emergency physician?

378
00:25:48,934 --> 00:25:50,147
Huh?

379
00:25:51,888 --> 00:25:54,908
No. Absolutely not.

380
00:25:55,006 --> 00:25:58,106
I don't know,
that's what it sounded like.

381
00:26:01,430 --> 00:26:03,689
Emergency medicine is beyond me.

382
00:26:05,933 --> 00:26:08,629
I don't have talent like Dr. Anno.

383
00:26:09,792 --> 00:26:12,034
Talent? Anno?

384
00:26:13,647 --> 00:26:14,847
Yes.

385
00:26:20,456 --> 00:26:26,532
Anno back in the day was barely
any different from you, Dr. Yakushiji.

386
00:26:27,798 --> 00:26:28,998
What?

387
00:26:31,341 --> 00:26:35,694
Being a doctor requires something
far more important than talent.

388
00:26:39,730 --> 00:26:42,492
Well, don't slack off too much.

389
00:27:03,072 --> 00:27:04,159
Yes, sir.

390
00:27:04,159 --> 00:27:08,429
A traffic accident victim incoming.
Please come right away.

391
00:27:08,918 --> 00:27:10,206
On my way.

392
00:27:24,139 --> 00:27:25,743
Ultrasound and X-ray, STAT.

393
00:27:37,029 --> 00:27:38,413
Akane?

394
00:27:42,438 --> 00:27:43,937
Akane!

395
00:27:45,160 --> 00:27:46,595
You know her?

396
00:27:49,226 --> 00:27:52,164
Don't push yourself.
Step back, Dr. Yakushiji.

397
00:27:53,536 --> 00:27:54,736
No...

398
00:27:56,989 --> 00:27:58,605
I'm fine.

399
00:28:00,766 --> 00:28:03,190
I can do this.

400
00:28:05,590 --> 00:28:06,631
Hematemesis!

401
00:28:06,631 --> 00:28:10,306
Heavy bleeding in the oral cavity.
Intubating before the airway's blocked.

402
00:28:10,306 --> 00:28:13,303
Liver's damaged.
May need a partial resection.

403
00:28:13,303 --> 00:28:14,507
Call Surgery.

404
00:28:14,879 --> 00:28:16,179
Kid, intubate.

405
00:28:16,867 --> 00:28:18,085
Okay.

406
00:28:22,140 --> 00:28:23,348
Intubate, now!

407
00:28:28,900 --> 00:28:30,260
Kid, stop the bleeding!

408
00:28:30,260 --> 00:28:32,624
Dr. Yakushiji, could you step out?

409
00:28:36,349 --> 00:28:39,770
At this rate,
we won't be able to save the patient.

410
00:28:53,372 --> 00:28:54,594
I'm sorry.

411
00:28:58,879 --> 00:28:59,913
The OR?

412
00:28:59,913 --> 00:29:02,109
No good. It won't
be free for two hours.

413
00:29:02,109 --> 00:29:05,308
Emergency surgery.
Prep a laparotomy and liver resection set.

414
00:29:05,308 --> 00:29:06,531
Understood.

415
00:29:20,269 --> 00:29:21,486
Tamotsu?

416
00:29:26,134 --> 00:29:27,354
Keita.

417
00:29:27,730 --> 00:29:31,074
So this is your hospital.
Thank God.

418
00:29:33,095 --> 00:29:35,428
Akane's gonna make it, right?

419
00:29:36,596 --> 00:29:38,228
She's not gonna die, right?

420
00:29:41,187 --> 00:29:43,628
You can save her, can't you?

421
00:29:45,343 --> 00:29:46,800
Please, save her.

422
00:29:52,345 --> 00:29:53,613
I'm sorry.

423
00:30:02,566 --> 00:30:07,386
Why? What are you apologizing for?

424
00:30:10,759 --> 00:30:17,279
The other doctors are treating her right now.

425
00:30:20,921 --> 00:30:22,607
You're a doctor too, right?

426
00:30:25,056 --> 00:30:28,597
If you're a doctor, then save Akane!

427
00:30:30,922 --> 00:30:32,744
Say something!

428
00:30:34,949 --> 00:30:36,465
Tamotsu!

429
00:30:41,499 --> 00:30:43,659
I want to save her too.

430
00:30:55,609 --> 00:30:57,983
But I can't.

431
00:31:01,232 --> 00:31:02,472
I'm sorry.

432
00:31:06,264 --> 00:31:08,095
I can't do anything.

433
00:31:13,074 --> 00:31:14,800
I'm so sorry.

434
00:31:27,994 --> 00:31:29,348
I...

435
00:31:32,703 --> 00:31:34,343
I can't do anything either.

436
00:31:44,549 --> 00:31:49,259
Why is it her and not me?

437
00:31:55,630 --> 00:31:59,759
Akane...Akane!

438
00:32:13,516 --> 00:32:14,736
Keita?

439
00:32:18,732 --> 00:32:20,030
What's wrong?

440
00:32:21,562 --> 00:32:22,789
Keita?

441
00:32:23,863 --> 00:32:25,084
Keita!

442
00:32:28,833 --> 00:32:30,157
Cardiac arrest.

443
00:32:36,002 --> 00:32:37,216
How?

444
00:32:38,483 --> 00:32:42,483
Patient crashed in the hallway.
Cardiac arrest!

445
00:32:42,890 --> 00:32:44,387
Cardiac arrest?

446
00:32:44,992 --> 00:32:47,953
What do we do?
We can't step away yet.

447
00:32:51,252 --> 00:32:52,290
Go help them.

448
00:32:52,290 --> 00:32:53,505
Yes, Doctor.

449
00:32:56,302 --> 00:32:57,539
Keita...

450
00:33:22,232 --> 00:33:23,440
Dr. Yakushiji!

451
00:33:26,522 --> 00:33:29,083
Doctor, what about cardiac compressions?

452
00:33:38,040 --> 00:33:39,520
Pull yourself together!

453
00:33:41,213 --> 00:33:45,838
Can't Dr. Anno come?

454
00:33:45,913 --> 00:33:49,319
Both doctors are in surgery
and can't leave.

455
00:33:51,505 --> 00:33:54,725
You're the only one
who can treat him.

456
00:33:56,472 --> 00:33:58,572
There's no one else!

457
00:34:01,206 --> 00:34:02,669
Give me orders!

458
00:34:05,065 --> 00:34:06,289
I can't.

459
00:34:09,818 --> 00:34:11,735
I can't save him.

460
00:34:16,093 --> 00:34:20,337
Dr. Anno, I can't do this.

461
00:34:21,065 --> 00:34:25,305
Please, save Keita!

462
00:34:25,930 --> 00:34:27,130
Metzenbaum.

463
00:34:30,673 --> 00:34:32,145
Dr. Anno!

464
00:34:52,283 --> 00:34:53,532
Keita...

465
00:34:57,151 --> 00:34:58,378
I'm sorry.

466
00:35:00,502 --> 00:35:04,402
Keita always said he was proud
to be your best friend.

467
00:35:05,317 --> 00:35:06,555
I'm sorry.

468
00:35:06,591 --> 00:35:11,449
I know it's tough having people's lives
in your hands, but I'm rooting for you.

469
00:35:11,449 --> 00:35:14,136
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

470
00:35:15,122 --> 00:35:17,001
I'm sorry.

471
00:35:24,379 --> 00:35:25,587
Kid!

472
00:35:29,216 --> 00:35:30,832
Who do you think you are?!

473
00:35:33,282 --> 00:35:35,534
Saying you can't is just giving up!

474
00:35:36,629 --> 00:35:39,309
You're choosing to let him die
with your own will!

475
00:35:40,310 --> 00:35:44,702
That's what a clueless rookie
with no knowledge or experience says!

476
00:35:45,776 --> 00:35:47,701
Are you just a rookie?!

477
00:35:57,560 --> 00:36:00,332
Your patient is on death's door.
None of that matters!

478
00:36:00,332 --> 00:36:01,784
Give me one more chance!

479
00:36:01,784 --> 00:36:05,746
There are no second chances
in life-or-death. Hesitation kills.

480
00:36:05,746 --> 00:36:09,707
Resident or not, take responsibility
for the life in front of you!

481
00:36:14,322 --> 00:36:18,602
Your patient is crying for help.
How can a doctor just give up?!

482
00:36:38,199 --> 00:36:39,417
I'll do it.

483
00:36:42,106 --> 00:36:44,066
I will save him!

484
00:36:46,946 --> 00:36:48,146
I'll take over!

485
00:36:48,539 --> 00:36:49,759
Please.

486
00:36:54,616 --> 00:36:55,876
Keita.

487
00:36:58,301 --> 00:36:59,541
Come back to me.

488
00:37:06,620 --> 00:37:08,307
Don't you die on me.

489
00:37:15,642 --> 00:37:18,102
You're getting married soon.

490
00:37:25,982 --> 00:37:27,310
15 minutes since clamping.

491
00:37:27,310 --> 00:37:28,470
Releasing the clamp.

492
00:37:28,470 --> 00:37:29,683
Keita!

493
00:37:31,614 --> 00:37:32,846
Hang in there!

494
00:37:35,157 --> 00:37:36,369
Hang in there!

495
00:37:38,417 --> 00:37:39,627
Hang in there!

496
00:37:43,964 --> 00:37:46,111
VF. Get the DC ready.

497
00:37:46,200 --> 00:37:47,524
Charge to 150.

498
00:37:53,495 --> 00:37:54,704
Charged.

499
00:37:57,103 --> 00:37:58,314
Clear!

500
00:38:19,462 --> 00:38:21,409
Heartbeat restored.

501
00:38:27,580 --> 00:38:30,442
Doctor, BP won't come back
above the 40s.

502
00:38:30,442 --> 00:38:35,105
Why? At this rate, we can't maintain
respiration or circulation.

503
00:38:35,326 --> 00:38:36,545
What do we do?

504
00:38:37,233 --> 00:38:40,993
Think. There has to be a cause.

505
00:38:42,612 --> 00:38:43,823
Think!

506
00:38:48,755 --> 00:38:51,202
Just got back to Japan yesterday.

507
00:38:51,282 --> 00:38:52,310
What's wrong?

508
00:38:52,310 --> 00:38:56,248
The flight back was so cramped,
my legs almost seized up.

509
00:39:01,120 --> 00:39:03,022
His left leg is red and swollen.

510
00:39:03,022 --> 00:39:07,869
A blood clot in the lower leg caused
swelling, then traveled to the lungs.

511
00:39:08,785 --> 00:39:12,685
The cardiac arrest may be pulmonary
embolism from economy class syndrome.

512
00:39:13,303 --> 00:39:14,339
Resuming clamping.

513
00:39:14,339 --> 00:39:15,543
Okay.

514
00:39:17,306 --> 00:39:21,861
Let's get a contrast CT for confirmation.
I'll maintain circulation with noradrenaline.

515
00:39:22,771 --> 00:39:23,813
Suture scissors.

516
00:39:23,813 --> 00:39:25,025
Here.

517
00:39:28,612 --> 00:39:30,689
Looks like that side's under control.

518
00:39:31,186 --> 00:39:34,269
We can't let our guard down
until the surgery's finished.

519
00:39:37,436 --> 00:39:38,648
3-0 silk.

520
00:39:49,820 --> 00:39:52,824
Well, maybe I'll go grab
something sweet.

521
00:39:55,256 --> 00:39:56,706
What is it at this hour?

522
00:39:57,811 --> 00:39:58,850
Hello?

523
00:39:58,850 --> 00:40:00,883
This is Yakushiji from Emergency.

524
00:40:00,883 --> 00:40:04,689
Suspected severe pulmonary embolism.
Vasopressors aren't raising the BP.

525
00:40:04,689 --> 00:40:07,249
Once CT confirms,
we'll need emergency surgery.

526
00:40:09,209 --> 00:40:10,416
Damn!

527
00:40:11,283 --> 00:40:14,588
Leave it to Surgery. Bring the patient
to the OR once confirmed.

528
00:40:14,588 --> 00:40:15,795
Thank you!

529
00:40:59,993 --> 00:41:01,274
How are the patients?

530
00:41:01,352 --> 00:41:03,994
They both seem stable.

531
00:41:04,200 --> 00:41:05,414
Good.

532
00:41:06,709 --> 00:41:08,105
Dr. Anno.

533
00:41:09,923 --> 00:41:11,412
Thank you so much.

534
00:41:13,126 --> 00:41:15,757
I didn't really do anything
worth thanking.

535
00:41:17,560 --> 00:41:18,807
Sorry.

536
00:41:20,818 --> 00:41:22,106
But...

537
00:41:24,369 --> 00:41:26,032
I truly am grateful.

538
00:41:36,587 --> 00:41:37,885
Well,

539
00:41:39,443 --> 00:41:41,903
you did pretty good yourself,
Dr. Yakushiji.

540
00:41:47,892 --> 00:41:49,098
Good work today.

541
00:42:03,010 --> 00:42:06,210
I want to be a doctor
like Dr. Anno.

542
00:42:07,205 --> 00:42:09,732
I'm nowhere close yet.

543
00:42:15,477 --> 00:42:18,277
But still, like her,

544
00:42:20,429 --> 00:42:22,391
I want to save lives.

545
00:42:50,904 --> 00:42:52,304
One, two, three!

546
00:43:01,919 --> 00:43:02,950
Gauze.

547
00:43:02,950 --> 00:43:04,378
She's bleeding badly!

548
00:43:05,068 --> 00:43:08,488
I'm going to die...

549
00:43:08,635 --> 00:43:11,674
It might be too late.

550
00:43:12,200 --> 00:43:13,233
No...

551
00:43:13,233 --> 00:43:15,037
There's nothing we can do.

552
00:43:15,646 --> 00:43:17,426
I won't make it...

553
00:43:21,120 --> 00:43:25,368
The patient is begging for help,
and you're giving up?!

554
00:43:28,292 --> 00:43:30,418
You did so well.

555
00:43:30,470 --> 00:43:36,677
You're safe now.
I will save you, no matter what.

556
00:44:10,639 --> 00:44:13,654
Would an adult really just
fall like that?

557
00:44:13,654 --> 00:44:16,148
Please just let him pass in peace!

558
00:44:16,148 --> 00:44:17,975
They don't want further treatment.

559
00:44:17,975 --> 00:44:19,531
He says he's not ready to die.

560
00:44:19,531 --> 00:44:22,639
- You can't even examine patients properly.
- Will it be okay?

561
00:44:22,639 --> 00:44:24,294
Never give up on life.
